<tr>
<td>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;">Are you getting a gift for your child but have no idea what kind of skateboard you should get? The good news is that it&rsquo;s not that complicated. All of our products pretty much fall into one of two categories: Longboards and Shortboards.</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #993300;"><strong><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;">What&rsquo;s the difference between a Longboard and a Shortboard you ask?</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;">Shortboards such as <a title="Skateboard Completes" href="http://www.scuffz.com/skateboards-1/" target="_top">trickboards</a> are generally used for street skating. The nose and tail of the board are raised allowing skilled skaters to perform tricks such as kick flips and ollies. <a title="Cheap Longboards" href="http://www.scuffz.com/longboards/" target="_top">Longboards</a> are generally used for cruising long distances. They can be used to perform tricks as well but of a different style.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;">We&rsquo;ll be asking you a few questions to determine which boards best fit your child&rsquo;s needs.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>
<p><span style="color: #993300;"><strong><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;"><a href="http://www.scuffz.com/checkered-complete-skateboard/" target="_self"><img src="http://www.scuffz.com/products/136/images/1381/checker_c__20859.1358277479.220.220.jpg" alt="Punked Checker Skateboard Complete" width="220" height="220" align="right" border="0" /></a>Is this your young child&rsquo;s first skateboard?</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;">If your child is between the ages of 5-10 we&rsquo;d recommend going with a <a title="Skateboard" href="http://www.scuffz.com/skateboards-1/" target="_top">trickbboard</a>. It&rsquo;s light enough for them to be able to maneuver it and its wide wheelbase provides the stability they need when first learning how to skate. In addition, trickboards are excellent for advanced skaters as well which means that this board will still be relevant as their skills improve. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;">We have a variety of trickboards but the most popular would be the <a href="http://www.scuffz.com/checkered-complete-skateboard/" target="_self">Punked Checker Skateboard Complete</a>. This new school skateboard comes with a mellow concave allowing for a more flat-footed skating style. The edges of the board are not so bowled compared to medium and steep concaves.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>
<p><span style="color: #993300;"><strong><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;"><a href="http://www.scuffz.com/kicktail-tsunami-complete/" target="_self"><img src="http://www.scuffz.com/products/155/images/837/KT_tsunami_C_pic_new__71089.1333995418.220.220.jpg" alt="Punked Kicktail Tsunami Longboard Complete" width="220" height="220" align="left" border="0" /></a>Is this your teenage child&rsquo;s first skateboard?</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;">If so we&rsquo;d recommend choosing a longboard. The bigger board gives more stability and generally has a smaller learning curve to get started. The <a title="Kicktail Longboard Completes" href="http://www.scuffz.com/longboard-kicktail-completes/">kicktail</a> is a great choice for beginners do to the fact that they have more maneuverability at low speeds. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;">A popular choice is the <a href="http://www.scuffz.com/kicktail-tsunami-complete/" target="_self">Punked Tsunami Kicktail Longboard Complete</a>. In addition to having a kicktail, it also has a medium concave that will help with big tricks, pivots, slides, ollies, and much more. The longer wheelbase gives more stability for downhill speedboarding while also giving more footspace when cruising.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>
<p><span style="color: #993300;"><strong><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;"><strong><strong><a href="http://www.scuffz.com/mini-cruiser-stained-complete/" target="_self"><img src="http://www.scuffz.com/products/151/images/721/mc_c_stained_gn__89258.1328298359.220.220.jpg" alt="Minicruiser Stained Complete" width="220" height="220" align="right" border="0" /></a></strong></strong>Does your child go to a large school and needs to get around campus?</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;">A Shortboard such as the <a title="Mini Cruiser Completes" href="http://www.scuffz.com/mini-cruisers/" target="_top">mini cruiser</a> is best suited for this scenario. Mini cruisers provide the best of both worlds. They&rsquo;re portable and stable! If your child needs something even more portable we also have <a title="Micro Cruisers" href="http://www.scuffz.com/micro-cruisers/" target="_top">micro cruisers</a>. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;">Currently our most popular Mini cruisers are the <a href="http://www.scuffz.com/mini-cruiser-stained-complete/" target="_self">Mini Cruiser Stained Completes</a>. These light-weight Punked Stained Mini Cruisers come fully assembled and ready to ride! Whether they're planning to cruise down the beach or navigate their way around campus, now they can do it without the burden of figuring out where to store it once they arrive.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>
<p><span style="color: #993300;"><strong><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;"><strong><a href="http://www.scuffz.com/drop-down-rasta-2-longboard-complete/" target="_self"><img src="http://www.scuffz.com/products/238/images/1159/DD_rasta2_C__32687.1350430094.220.220.jpg" alt="Punked Dropdown Rasta Longboard Complete" width="220" height="220" align="left" border="0" /></a></strong>Will this board be used for traveling large distances?</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;">In this case we&rsquo;d recommend a <a title="Drop Through Longboards" href="http://www.scuffz.com/longboard-drop-through-complete/" target="_top">drop through</a> or <a title="Drop Down Longboards" href="http://www.scuffz.com/longboard-drop-down-completes/">drop down</a> longboard. Both these boards have a lower center of gravity making it more stable at faster speeds. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;">A popular drop down is the <a href="http://www.scuffz.com/drop-down-rasta-2-longboard-complete/" target="_self">Punked Rasta 2 Longboard Complete</a>. This longboard is unique in that the deck is lower at the center than where the trucks are mounted. This lowers your center of gravity giving you more stability at greater speeds making it great for speed-boarding.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</td>
