<tr>
<td>
<p><span style="color: #993300;"><strong><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;"><strong><a href="http://www.scuffz.com/punked-city-cruiser/" target="_self"><img src="http://www.scuffz.com/products/173/images/822/city_cruiser_all__30157.1333755902.220.220.jpg" alt="Punked City Vinyl Cruiser" width="220" height="220" align="right" border="0" /></a></strong>Does your child like to stand out from the crowd?</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;">If so, we&rsquo;d highly recommend the <a title="Vinyl Plastic Cruisers" href="http://www.scuffz.com/vinyl-cruisers/" target="_top">vinyl cruisers</a>. They were very popular back in the 70&rsquo;s and now they&rsquo;ve been brought back! These plastic-injection molded decks are the smallest boards that we carry measuring at 22.5 x 6 inches. They're tough, durable, lightweight, and resistant to corrosion. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;">Currently the most popular vinyl cruiser is the <a href="http://www.scuffz.com/punked-city-cruiser/" target="_self">Punked City Cruiser</a> which comes in four colors. These come packaged with a sticker pack allowing them to custimize there boards. In addition, the box that these come in doubles as a traveling storage case! </span></p>
