<p><span style="color: #993300;"><strong><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;"><a href="http://www.scuffz.com/ironfist-youth-skateboard-helmet/" target="_self"><img src="http://www.scuffz.com/products/145/images/564/jr_helmets__95277.1317165265.220.220.jpg" alt="Ironfist Youth Helmets" width="220" height="220" align="left" border="0" /></a>Does your child have any safety equipment?</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;">It&rsquo;s important to remember that skateboarding can be very dangerous if your child doesn&rsquo;t have the proper safety equipment. Regardless of skill level, we suggest they wear a <a title="Skateboard Helmets and Pads" href="http://www.scuffz.com/helmets-pads/" target="_top">helmet</a> to protect them from falls. We have helmets for both <a href="http://www.scuffz.com/ironfist-youth-skateboard-helmet/" target="_self">youth</a> and <a href="http://www.scuffz.com/ironfist-skateboard-helmet/" target="_self">adults</a>. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;">We also have a <a href="http://www.scuffz.com/yocaher-skateboard-protector-pads-tri-pack/" target="_self">protection pad set</a> for elbows, knees, and wrists.<br /> </span></p>
